27 (c) (1) The probationary employment qualifications established under
28 subsection (b)(13) of this section shall allow an individual to be employed as a child care
29 teacher during a probationary period if the individual:
30 (i) 1. Is enrolled in approved pre–service training;
31 2. Successfully completes the required 90 hours of the
32 approved pre–service training within 6 months after being hired; and
33 3. Holds an associate degree or a bachelor’s degree in:

